    <section class="left-column">
      <h2>Batanes</h2>
      <p>1. Geography and Location:</p>
       
       <p> Located in the northernmost part of the Philippines, Batanes is an archipelago composed of 10 islands, with the main islands being Batan, Sabtang, and Itbayat.</p>
   
        The province is geographically closer to Taiwan than to Manila, making it more isolated and distinct from the rest of the country.</p>
        <p>Batanes is known for its rolling hills, grassy plains, rugged coastlines, and stone houses.</p>

    </section>

    <section class="right-column">
      <h2>Palawan</h2>
      <p>Palawan:
        Located in the western part of the Philippines, Palawan is a large island province that spans from the South China Sea in the west to the Sulu Sea in the east.</p>

        It is made up of a main island and more than 1,700 smaller islands and islets, including popular destinations like El Nido, Coron, and Puerto Princesa.</p>
       
     Palawan is famous for its pristine beaches, limestone cliffs, crystal-clear lagoons, and rich marine life.</p>
   
    </section>
